<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbddf1dcf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s6954"><num value="6954">§ 6954.</num><heading> Technology promotion</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Commerce is authorized to evaluate the commercial feasibility of resource recovery facilities and to publish the results of such evaluation, and to develop a data base for purposes of assisting persons in choosing such a system.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbddf1dd0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/272/tII/s5004">Pub. L. 89–272, title II, § 5004</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/94/580/s2">Pub. L. 94–580, § 2</ref>, <date date="1976-10-21">Oct. 21, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/2821">90 Stat. 2821</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
